<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5875" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λόχος</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λεχ</span>): place of <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ambush</span>, act of
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">lying in wait;</span> said of the Trojan horse, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.513</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            4.277</span></i>; also of the party forming the
          <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ambuscade</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 8.522</span></i>;
          and of any armed company, <i><span class="en">Od. 20.49</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; λόχος γέροντος</span>, ‘means of
          entrapping’ the old man of the sea, <i><span class="en">Od.
            4.395</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">.— λόχονδε</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">upon an ambuscade,
            into the ambush</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.227</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 14.217</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
